1
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:10,120
River? Are you okay? Talk to me.

2
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:14,000
Okay. Um, uh...
Breathe, breathe, come on.

3
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,760
Got to keep breathing. Uh...

4
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:17,520
(PANTING)

5
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:26,200
River, you are holding your breath.
(GROANS)

6
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,840
You're a fine one to talk about holding.

7
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:30,480
How many hands do you have?

8
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:32,080
Get up! What are you doing?

9
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:35,040
-Who's shooting at you?
-Oh, just a few Sontarans.

10
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,600
Chased me halfway across the galaxy.

11
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:38,920
I probably shouldn't have asked
them if they were on a hen night.

12
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,600
-River, you can't do things like that.
-Or what?

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,800
You've already had me banged up in jail
for five years.

14
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:46,040
What else are you going to do? Spank me?

15
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:47,920
-Now, that...
-Doctor,

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,160
have you brought someone else here?

17
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,200
Does anyone agree to wear that dress?

18
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:53,880
Where is she?

19
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:55,600
River, think it through.

20
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,080
This happened the
last time we were here.

21
00:00:57,160 --> 00:00:58,880
-You brought someone else.
-No, I didn't.

22
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:01,000
Yes, you did.
I heard you talking to her.

23
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:02,600
It's the same night!

24
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,280
Doctor, were you talking to someone?

25
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,080
No, no, just me.

26
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:11,960
-Were you talking to someone?
-No, no, dear. Just me.

27
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,880
You nostalgic idiot.

28
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:23,360
You just can't keep away, can you?

29
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:27,240
Doctor, why have you brought
another one of these?

30
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,120
Who else is here?

31
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:36,280
River, could you just check
the light on top?

32
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,520
I think the bulb needs changing.

33
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,480
-The bulb?
-Mmm-hmm.

34
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,320
-Who were you talking to?
-You.

35
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,880
I'm talking to you.
Back to Storm Cage, Dr Song.

36
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:53,480
Oh, at least give me a lift. You know
what this thing does to my hair.

37
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,720
-It's always like that.
-(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

38
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,440
(CHUCKLES)

39
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,960
The light's fine. I don't know
what you're talking about.

40
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,880
No, River, wrong Tardis.

41
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:05,400
I'm parked round the back.

42
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,520
-(GASPS)
-Younger version.

43
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,200
Two of you!

44
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:12,320
-The mind races, does it not?
-Come on, we'll be late.

45
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,680
He's taking me to the
Singing Towers of Darillium.

46
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,440
He's been promising for ages.

47
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,360
The first time we met her at the library
when she...

48
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,080
Died, yes.

49
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:29,520
She said the last time she saw us
was at Darillium.

50
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,200
Is that now?

51
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:37,080
Spoilers! Good luck tonight.

52
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,360
You, too.

53
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,440
Yeah.

54
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:52,120
There's two of you! The mind races.

55
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:54,760
Right, come on, you.
Let's go and see the stars.

56
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:57,840
-But I haven't changed.
-And you never will, River.

57
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,720
Never ever.

58
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,520
What was the other you doing here?

59
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:05,240
-Sorry, can't say.
-What's that word you use?

60
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,960
(LAUGHS) Spoilers.

61
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,560
-I like that word.
-I thought you might.

62
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:14,080
(SIGHS) Doctor, you and your secrets.

63
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,280
-You'll be the death of me.
-Mmm.

